<article id="post-7" class="post-7 page type-page status-publish post">

	<div class="entry-main">

		
					<header class="entry-header">
													<h1 class="entry-title">Philippine Federation of Chemistry Societies</h1>
							</header><!-- .entry-header -->
		
		<div class="entry-content">
			
<p>The Philippine Federation of Chemistry Societies was organized in 1988 to serve as an umbrella organization for the four chemistry societies in the Philippines:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list"><li>Kapisanang Kimika ng Pilipinas (KKP)</li><li>Integrated Chemists of the Philippines (ICP)</li><li>Philippine Association of Chemistry Teachers (PACT)</li><li>Philippine Association of Chemistry Students (PACS)</li></ul>



<p>Through the four organizations, the PFCS is able to reach and provide service to professional chemists, chemical technicians, educators, students, and professionals in the allied disciplines.</p>



<p>The PFCS is a non-profit, non-stock corporation which is registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission of the Philippines.</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->

		
	</div>

</article><!-- #post-7 -->

			
		
